<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Civil Rights Photography Exhibit</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
    }

    header {
      background-color: #111;
      color: white;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .intro {
      padding: 20px;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: auto;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .gallery {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 15px;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .photo {
      background: white;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      cursor: pointer;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    }

    .photo img {
      width: 100%;
      display: block;
    }

    .caption {
      padding: 10px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    /* Modal */
    .modal {
      display: none;
      position: fixed;
      z-index: 10;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    }

    .modal-content {
      margin: 10% auto;
      display: block;
      max-width: 80%;
    }

    .modal-caption {
      text-align: center;
      color: white;
      padding: 10px;
    }

    .close {
      position: absolute;
      top: 20px;
      right: 40px;
      color: white;
      font-size: 30px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>Civil Rights Photography: Witnessing Change</h1>
</header>

<section class="intro">
  <p>
    This virtual exhibit explores the role of photography in shaping public understanding of the Civil Rights Movement. 
    These images document protest, resistance, and everyday courage.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="gallery">

  <div class="photo" onclick="openModal(this)">
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400" alt="Birmingham Protest">
    <div class="caption">Birmingham, 1963 – Protesters facing police violence.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="photo" onclick="openModal(this)">
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400" alt="March on Washington">
    <div class="caption">March on Washington, 1963 – A crowd gathers for justice.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="photo" onclick="openModal(this)">
    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400" alt="Selma">
    <div class="caption">Selma to Montgomery, 1965 – Crossing the Edmund Pettus Bridge.</div>
  </div>

</section>

<!-- Modal -->
<div id="modal" class="modal" onclick="closeModal()">
  <span class="close">&times;</span>
  <img class="modal-content" id="modal-img">
  <div class="modal-caption" id="modal-caption"></div>
</div>

<script>
  function openModal(element) {
    document.getElementById("modal").style.display = "block";
    document.getElementById("modal-img").src = element.querySelector("img").src;
    document.getElementById("modal-caption").innerText = element.querySelector(".caption").innerText;
  }

  function closeModal() {
    document.getElementById("modal").style.display = "none";
  }
</script>

<section class="compare-section">
  <h2>Comparing Perspectives</h2>

  <div class="compare-container">
    <img src="image1.jpg" class="compare-img">
    <img src="image2.jpg" class="compare-img overlay" id="overlay">

    <input type="range" min="0" max="100" value="50" id="slider">
  </div>

  <p class="caption">
    Compare media portrayals of the same event. How does framing shape public perception?
  </p>
</section>

<section class="timeline">
  <h2>Civil Rights Timeline</h2>

  <input type="range" min="0" max="2" value="0" id="timelineSlider">

  <div id="timelineContent">
    <h3>1963 – Birmingham Campaign</h3>
    <p>Images of police brutality shocked the nation and drew global attention.</p>
  </div>
</section>


</body>
</html>
